 present day, through successive waves of immigration, Jews have asserted the compatibility of their French identity with various versions of Jewish particularity, including Zionism. This remarkable view in microcosm of the modern Jewish experience will interest general readers and scholars alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aJewsxHistoryxFrance. 0aJewszFrancexHistory. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520919297?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520919297423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520919297/original  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles